JOHANNESBURG - The North Gauteng High Court is set to hear former Hawks boss Berning Ntlemeza's plea for a restraining order against Police Minister Fikile Mbalula on Tuesday.Ntlemeza wants the court to stop Mbalula from preventing his return to work.The two are involved in a standoff, with the police minister demanding that Ntlemeza return the state vehicle and cellphone.Ntlemeza insists that no court has the power to remove him from office and only Parliament can facilitate his dismissal.READ: Ntlemeza heading to Supreme CourtThe former Hawks boss says he s served the country for 35 years as a policeman and doesn t deserve to the treatment he's getting. eNCA